- Smart contracts are written in native Python without transpilation
- Contract names must follow pattern: `^con_[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$`
- Contract names must start with 'con_' prefix (except system contracts)
- Contract names must be lowercase, max 64 characters
- Cannot use '_' as prefix for variables or functions
- Follow standard Python naming conventions
- Use descriptive names for clarity
- A contract cannot be deployed by another contract
- XIAN is the currency of the Xian blockchain (never mention TAU or Lamden)